Gaara

Target IP: 192.168.170.142

Scanning



From the scans above, only two TCP ports are open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP. I will start my enumeration with the HTTP.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP


We are presented the webpage above on port 80. The source-code of the HTML page does not provide anything use either. After trying multiple wordslists, I had no luck.

Port 22: SSH

Using hydra, I was able to bruteforce the SSH application with the username as gaara.

Exploitation


gaara:iloveyou2 credentials worked. Now I have a foothold on the machine.

Privilege Escalation


It looks like we have two choices to elevate our privileges: gdb or gimp-2.10.


And I gained a root shell by using gdb. The command I used is ./gdb -nx -ex 'python import os; os.execl("/bin/sh", "sh", "-p")' -ex quit.

Flags


The local.txt flag once I gained foothold on the machine with SSH.


The proof.txt flag once I used gdb to elevate my privileges to root.
